<h1>Free Game Engines (No Subscription Priority)</h1>
<p>This page lists game engines that are <strong>free to start</strong>, focusing on long-term usability, freedom, and low maintenance.</p>

<div class="engine">
<h2>Godot (100% Free & Open Source)</h2>
<p><strong>Cost:</strong> Free forever, no royalties</p>
<p>Best choice for indie developers who want full control without licensing risk.</p>
</div>

<div class="engine">
<h2>Roblox</h2>
<p><strong>Cost:</strong> Free platform, revenue share on earnings</p>
<p>Ideal for social and multiplayer games with built-in audience.</p>
</div>

<div class="engine">
<h2>Core Engine</h2>
<p><strong>Cost:</strong> Free to use, platform-based monetization</p>
<p>Fast multiplayer prototyping inside Core ecosystem.</p>
</div>

<div class="engine">
<h2>Unity (Free Tier)</h2>
<p><strong>Cost:</strong> Free below revenue threshold</p>
<p>Strong cross-platform support but licensing terms should be monitored.</p>
</div>

<div class="engine">
<h2>Unreal Engine</h2>
<p><strong>Cost:</strong> Free to use, royalty after threshold</p>
<p>High-end visuals, heavier workflow.</p>
</div>

<p class="note">Last updated: 2025 • Static page • No tracking • No ads</p>

